quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  27,56,"But the only response of his people was to say, “Evict Lot’s folk from your town; indeed, they are a few people who always keep themselves clean.”"
  27,57,"So We saved him and his family, except for his wife, whom We destined to be of those who lingered behind."
  27,58,"And We rained upon them a rain, and so evil was the rain of the forewarned."
  27,59,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “Praise be to Allah and peace be upon His servants whom He has elected. Is Allah better or what <span class=""h"">they<sup foot_note=""80745"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">associate</span>?”"
  27,60,"Or who<i class=""s"">(else then) </i>is the one who created the heavens and the earth, and sent down to you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>from the sky water with which We{1}germinated gardens full of beauty, whose trees you could not have germinated? Is there any other god with Allah? Rather, they are a people who equate{2}.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 3rd person to 1st person.|2:Equate others with God.
  27,61,"Or who<i class=""s"">(else then) </i>is the one who made the earth habitable and made rivers flow through it and set firm mountains for it and placed a partition between the two seas? Is there any other god with Allah? Rather, most of them do not know."
  27,62,"Or who<i class=""s"">(else then) </i>is the one who responds to someone in need when he calls upon Him and relieves evil and makes you successors on earth? Is there any other god with Allah? Little do <span class=""h"">you remind<sup foot_note=""80748"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">yourselves</span>."
  27,63,"Or who<i class=""s"">(else then) </i>is the one who guides you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>through the darkness<i class=""s"">(es) </i>of the land and the sea, and who sends the <span class=""h"">winds<sup foot_note=""80749"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>as <span class=""h"">heralds</span><span class=""h"">of glad tidings<sup foot_note=""80750"" class=""qiraat"">2</sup> </span>before His mercy? Is there any other god with Allah? Most High is Allah above what they associate."
